                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d766">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2916: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>155. At reopening of University yesterday morning students were permitted to hold
                    mass meeting without molestation by authorities. Leaders incited attack upon
                    administration building following which group marched without permit toward
                    center of city for purpose of arousing students at normal school and institute.
                    One of the police who were attempting to stop demonstration killed by unknown
                    person. All students arrested were released last night.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
